    <p class="articletitle">
        Getting Started in Software Development</p>
    <p class="articlesub">
        Series Index</p>
    <p>
        This series explores both the professional and technical realities of a career 
        in software development. I detail some of the professional and technical 
        requirements and give some advice on how to plan for the long term.</p>
    <p>
        <a href="../Articles/201206190957.aspx">Part One: Software Development is More 
        than Writing Code</a></p>
    <p class="indent">
        Software development is very much an engineering discipline. More than writing 
        code, it&#39;s about the search for solutions to real-world problems and takes a 
        certain mindset to truly enjoy.</p>
    <p>
        <a href="../Articles/201206200922.aspx">Part Two: Finding a Career in Software 
        Development</a></p>
    <p class="indent">
        In this Information Age, it&#39;s easier than ever to take charge of your own 
        education and learn any subject that interests you, including software 
        development. Like with many other things, however, it&#39;s a commitment that 
        requires dedication. Success requires a fair amount of initiative as well.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="../Articles/201206252154.aspx">Part Three: A Quick Look at Programming 
        Technologies</a></p>
    <p class="indent">
        Software development is a large and diverse field with a lot of technologies to 
        choose from. The first step is to decide what type of programming interests you 
        the most, find the tools and start learning.</p>
    <p>
        <a href="../Articles/201206281110.aspx">Part Four: Long-term Strategy</a></p>
    <p class="indent">
        As quickly as technology changes, individual products have a way of staying 
        around for awhile and the knowledge you gain with one technology can help you 
        with the advancements that follow. 
    </p>
